'''Nielíqui''' was a [[Valar|Vala]] maiden according to the early version of the [[legendarium]] in ''[[The Book of Lost Tales]]''. 

She was the daughter of [[Oromë]] and [[Vána]].<ref>{{MC|Secret}}, p. 220 (note 9)</ref><ref>{{LT1|Index}}, p. 288</ref> She also enjoyed dancing through her father's [[Woods of Oromë|woods]] and [[Ómar]] would sometimes accompany her by singing along.<ref>{{LT1|III}}, p. 75</ref> It is said that: "where her tears fell snowdrops sprang, where her feet touched as she laughed daffodils blossomed".<ref name=Nie/>

== Etymology ==
Aside from the form '''''Nielíqui''''', there were other variations on her name: '''''Nielikki''''' or '''''Nyelikki''''', and '''''Nieliqi'''''.<ref name=Nie>{{PE|12}}, p. 69</ref> ''Nielikki'' was perhaps intended to be a "pet-name form" of ''Nieliqi''.<ref>{{PE|16}}, p. 90</ref> She was also called '''''Wendine''''' (meaning "Little Maiden" in [[Qenya]]).<ref>{{PE|14}}, p. 15</ref>

